.TH PUTS 3 "2025" "Nightingale" "Nightingale Library Functions"
.SH NAME
puts, fputs \- output a string
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <stdio.h>
.PP
.BI "int puts(const char *" s ");"
.BI "int fputs(const char *" s ", FILE *" stream ");"
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.BR puts ()
writes the string
.I s
and a trailing newline to
.IR stdout .
.PP
.BR fputs ()
writes the string
.I s
to
.IR stream ,
without its trailing null byte ('\\0'), and without appending a newline.
.SH RETURN VALUE
.BR puts ()
and
.BR fputs ()
return a nonnegative number on success, or
.B EOF
on error.
.SH NOTES
Note the difference between
.BR puts ()
and
.BR fputs ():
.BR puts ()
always appends a newline, while
.BR fputs ()
does not.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR printf (3),
.BR fopen (3),
.BR write (2)
